# Supabase Database Queries

The Supabase client provides a PostgREST-powered query builder for CRUD operations with filters, joins, and pagination.

## Select (Read)

```typescript
// Select all columns
const { data, error } = await supabase
  .from('posts')
  .select('*');

// Select specific columns
const { data } = await supabase
  .from('posts')
  .select('id, title, created_at');

// Select with count
const { data, count } = await supabase
  .from('posts')
  .select('*', { count: 'exact' });

// Select a single row
const { data } = await supabase
  .from('posts')
  .select('*')
  .eq('id', postId)
  .single();
```

## Insert (Create)

```typescript
// Insert one row
const { data, error } = await supabase
  .from('posts')
  .insert({ title: 'Hello', body: 'World', user_id: userId })
  .select();

// Insert multiple rows
const { data, error } = await supabase
  .from('posts')
  .insert([
    { title: 'Post 1', body: 'Body 1' },
    { title: 'Post 2', body: 'Body 2' },
  ])
  .select();
```

## Update

```typescript
const { data, error } = await supabase
  .from('posts')
  .update({ title: 'Updated Title' })
  .eq('id', postId)
  .select();
```

## Upsert (Insert or Update)

```typescript
const { data, error } = await supabase
  .from('posts')
  .upsert(
    { id: postId, title: 'Upserted', body: 'Content' },
    { onConflict: 'id' }
  )
  .select();
```

## Delete

```typescript
const { error } = await supabase
  .from('posts')
  .delete()
  .eq('id', postId);
```

## Filters

```typescript
// Equality
.eq('status', 'published')

// Not equal
.neq('status', 'draft')

// Greater than / less than
.gt('views', 100)
.gte('views', 100)
.lt('views', 1000)
.lte('views', 1000)

// In a list
.in('status', ['published', 'archived'])

// Pattern matching
.like('title', '%hello%')
.ilike('title', '%hello%')  // case-insensitive

// Is null / not null
.is('deleted_at', null)
.not('deleted_at', 'is', null)

// Range
.range(0, 9)  // rows 0-9 (first 10)

// Array contains
.contains('tags', ['javascript', 'react'])
.containedBy('tags', ['javascript', 'react', 'nextjs'])

// Full-text search
.textSearch('title', 'hello world', { type: 'websearch' })

// JSON filtering
.eq('metadata->theme', 'dark')

// OR conditions
.or('status.eq.published,views.gt.100')
```

## Ordering and Pagination

```typescript
const { data } = await supabase
  .from('posts')
  .select('*')
  .order('created_at', { ascending: false })
  .range(0, 19);  // First 20 rows

// Multiple order columns
.order('status', { ascending: true })
.order('created_at', { ascending: false })

// Limit
.limit(10)
```

## Foreign Key Joins

PostgREST auto-detects foreign keys and enables relationship queries:

```typescript
// One-to-many: get posts with their comments
const { data } = await supabase
  .from('posts')
  .select(`
    id, title,
    comments (
      id, body, created_at
    )
  `);

// Many-to-one: get posts with their author
const { data } = await supabase
  .from('posts')
  .select(`
    id, title,
    author:profiles (
      id, full_name, avatar_url
    )
  `);

// Nested joins
const { data } = await supabase
  .from('posts')
  .select(`
    id, title,
    comments (
      id, body,
      author:profiles (
        full_name
      )
    )
  `);

// Filter on joined table
const { data } = await supabase
  .from('posts')
  .select('id, title, comments!inner(id, body)')
  .eq('comments.body', 'Great post!');
```

## RPC (Postgres Functions)

Call server-side Postgres functions:

```typescript
// Call a function
const { data, error } = await supabase
  .rpc('get_top_posts', {
    limit_count: 10,
    category: 'tech',
  });
```

Define the function in SQL:
```sql
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION get_top_posts(
  limit_count integer DEFAULT 10,
  category text DEFAULT NULL
)
RETURNS SETOF posts AS $$
  SELECT *
  FROM posts
  WHERE (category IS NULL OR posts.category = get_top_posts.category)
  ORDER BY views DESC
  LIMIT limit_count;
$$ LANGUAGE sql STABLE;
```

## Error Handling

```typescript
const { data, error } = await supabase
  .from('posts')
  .select('*');

if (error) {
  console.error('Query failed:', error.message);
  console.error('Code:', error.code);     // Postgres error code
  console.error('Details:', error.details);
  console.error('Hint:', error.hint);
  return;
}

// data is typed and non-null here
console.log(data);
```

## Important Patterns

- **Always check `error`** — the SDK never throws; errors come in the `error` field
- **Chain `.select()` after insert/update/upsert** to get back the affected rows
- **Use `.single()` for one row** — returns object instead of array, errors if 0 or 2+ rows
- **Use `.maybeSingle()`** — like `.single()` but returns null instead of error for 0 rows
- **Filters are AND by default** — use `.or()` for OR conditions
- **RLS applies to all queries** with the anon key — see [[supabase/rls]]
